----------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Requirement
----------------------------------------------------------------------

emacs22 | emacs23 | emacs-snapshot
ibus (>= 1.2.0)
python-ibus (>= 1.2.0)
python-xlib

----------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Installation
----------------------------------------------------------------------

i) Common settings

Save this file as ibus.el and byte-compile in a directory that is
listed in load-path, and also save ibus_el_agent.py somewhere in
your system.

Put the following in your .emacs file:

 (require 'ibus)
 (add-hook 'after-init-hook 'ibus-mode-on)

If ibus.el and ibus_el_agent.py are saved in different directories,
add a setting to the above as follows:

 (setq ibus-agent-file-name "/PATH/TO/ibus_el_agent.py")

To disable XIM in Emacs, put the following in ~/.Xresources:

 Emacs*useXIM: false

and restart X session or execute a shell command:

 xrdb ~/.Xresources

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

ii) Using ibus-anthy

To using kana input method with jp106 keyboard, add the following to
.emacs file:

 (setq ibus-use-kana-onbiki-key t)

If you'd like to use thumb shift input method, you must specify the
simultaneous pressing time as:

 (setq ibus-ibus-simultaneous-pressing-time 0.1)

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

iii) Using ibus-chewing

Please set input style to "in application window" in ibus-chewing's
configuration dialog.

